That regex is saying &quot;match anything that is not one of these digits&quot;. 4 is not one of those digits, so the string matches. If you want it to say &quot;match anything that does not include any of these digits&quot;, you want to test that every character matches that pattern from start to finish:

    /^[^01235689]*$/.test(+n);

(That means &quot;match anything that starts with any amount of characters not in this set and then ends, with nothing else in between&quot;.)

